{
  "text": "In acute right-sided diverticulitis, the clinical presentation is usually indistinguishable from acute appendicitis. On ultrasound, the inflamed diverticulum is seen as an out-pouching arising from the right colon, containing either fluid or a faecolith, surrounded by echogenic inflamed fat ( Figure 6 ). Some studies have shown ultrasound to have a similar diagnostic accuracy to CT imaging. [CITATION_1] Recognising this condition is crucial as this can usually be managed conservatively with intravenous antibiotics and settles without surgery.",
